article.description: Burrell hits go-ahead, Holy Cross defeats Lafayette 74-73
article.headline: Burrell hits go-ahead, Holy Cross defeats Lafayette 74-73
article.linkText: Burrell hits go-ahead, Holy Cross defeats Lafayette 74-73
article.story: WORCESTER, Mass. -- Justin Burrell scored the go-ahead layup with seven seconds remaining to lead Holy Cross to a 74-73 win over Lafayette on Wednesday night. Nick Lindner hit two free throws to give Lafayette a one-point lead with 22 second left, and after Burrell gave Holy Cross the edge, Seth Hinrichs missed a final attempt from 3-point range. Malachi Alexander finished with 17 points and four rebounds and Malcolm Miller had 13 points, including 3-of-3 shooting from 3-point range for the Crusaders (7-10, 2-5 Patriot). Dan Trist tallied 18 points and eight rebounds, Hinrichs had 14 and 10 and both Monty Boykins and Lindner added 12 for the Leopards (11-7, 3-4). Joey Ptasinski scored three points to put him over the 1,000-point mark, joining teammates Hinrichs and Trist. There were six lead changes after halftime and the Crusaders' six-point lead early in the second was the largest of the half.
